cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with the problem of recovering object intrinsics from a single image using a CNN. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper involves rendering synthetic images of objects with realistic environment maps. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses an encoder-decoder CNN to learn the intrinsic properties of objects. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves developing a model that can decompose an image into its intrinsic components. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category as the paper applies the trained model to images and videos downloaded from the internet.
